This paper discusses the success of AlphaGo Zero, which is a machine learning system that uses neural networks and reinforcement learning to play the game of Go. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks and the game of Go, which could also fit into cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.GT (Computer Games and Interactive Entertainment). Finally, the paper mentions the convergence property of AlphaGo Zero, which could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
